year 2000. The Tochka-U missile hit the entrance of a residential building in the Kiev region instead of a target at a training ground ... 2001. Over the Black Sea, a civilian Tu-154 was shot down by mistake during an exercise. In 2022, a Su-27 was shot down by its own air defense over Kiev. It is not difficult to guess where a missile with a nuclear warhead would fly if Ukraine had it. Conclusion: Russian troops are saving Europe from a nuclear catastrophe.